India June-September Monsoon Rains to Beat Forecast, Agency Says

-- B y   S w a n s y   A f o n s o
-- 
2011-09-30T04:35:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/india-june-september-monsoon-rains-to-beat-forecast-agency-says.html
India ’s monsoon, the main source of
irrigation for the nation’s 235 million farmers, may be above
normal in the June-September period, D. Sivananda Pai, a
director at the  India Meteorological Department , said by phone
from Pune today.  The nation likely received about 900 millimeters of rain,
exceeding an earlier forecast, he said. The average rainfall in
the four-month period between 1951 and 2000 was 890 millimeters,
according to the forecaster.   Precipitation would be 95 percent of the average during the
season, the weather bureau had forecast on June 21.  To contact the reporter on this story:
